I have two options how assets(positon/scale/rotation) can stored.
a) four points, each represents one corner
b) width, height + 3x3 matrix

Seems like matrix could simplify a lot of transformations but at the same time
I need to store points with UV coordinates anyway.

Thats why for now I'm going to stick with storing assets in a from of four points, each point is x,y,u,v.
For transformations like scaling, rotations the matricies will be used.
For transition is not useful since it's super easy to just add cursor position to points.

This way we can share same transformation data(bounds [4]PointUV)
between points(vector graphic) and distance field(raster).

